com.unvired.core
Class RuntimeEngine

java.lang.Object
  com.unvired.core.RuntimeEngine

public class RuntimeEngine
extends java.lang.Object

RuntimeEngine is used to initialize the application when the application starts. Initializing the application when the application starts is mandatory. Without the initialization the application cannot function.

Usage:

Call the function initialize(...) before:
  1. Accessing the database
  2. Accessing the synchronization / communication layer

Example:

 String appName = "SALES_ORDER"; // Should be same as the application name in the Meta Data xml file. Should ideally be declared as a constant in a Constants class file and accessed
 InputStream metaDataXml = this.getResources().openRawResource(R.raw.metadata); // metadata.xml is in the folder 'raw'
 
 RuntimeEngine runtimeEngine = RuntimeEngine.getInstance();
 runtimeEngine.initialize(this, appName, metaDataXml);
  // this - Current Activity's context. Assumes that the function call is made in an Activity. Hence 'this'
  // appName - name of the application
  // metadataXml - Meta Data of the application (data model)
RuntimeEngine is a singleton and can be accessed using the static method getInstance().
